				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The Irem M72 (R-Type I and II arcade hardware) built in 1987 has 512 colors and actually 15 bit color, although the CPS1 from the same time which was more powerful in about every way used 12 bit color. Is there some sort of weird correlation with hardware from 1987 and 384 pixel wide displays?</div><br />Perhaps 1987 is when CPU clock speeds hit 8 MHz. The video chip often shares a crystal with the CPU, and a plausible picture width for an 8 MHz dot clock on a 15.7 kHz horizontal frequency is 384 pixels.</div>

